  "definitions": [
    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "(springs), a place “near to Salim,” at which John baptized. (John 3:23) It was evidently west of the Jordan, comp. (John 3:22) with John 3:26 and with John 1:28 And abounded in water. This is indicated by the name, which is merely a Greek version of a Chaldee word signifying “springs.” AEnon is given in the Onomasticon as eight miles south of Scythopolis, “near Salem and the Jordan.”",
